From 7f52b43edbc66daa90f11f35c51e740985c10909 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 15:40:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add form-based single-student assessment input

Adds a third input mode alongside Chat and Upload: a structured Form where
a user types one student's academic fields directly and gets an instant risk
assessment.

Backend
- New POST /predict/form endpoint (sync) that validates required fields per
  prediction type, runs risk_service.assess, and persists the result to the
  conversations collection tagged source="form" (with optional name/studentId)
  so it flows into overview stats, sessions, and student detail.
- Overview/sessions/student services now label form-sourced records as
  "Form Assessment" and report source "form".

Frontend
- New FormPanel component with a prediction-type toggle (rule-based: 7 fields,
  ML: 17 fields) rendered from field metadata mirroring the training data,
  client-side validation, and the shared result card.
- predictForm added to the API client contract, HTTP client, and mock client.
- Form mode wired into NewAssessment; Dashboard/AllSessions handle the new
  "form" session type (icon, navigation, risk badge, delete via conversations).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
